From: Armbian
Subject: orangepi-zero: enable USB host (ehci2/ohci2) for USB boot

The board DT now comes from dts/upstream (OF_UPSTREAM), so u-boot-specific tweaks
belong in a <dtname>-u-boot.dtsi overlay (auto-applied on top of the upstream DT),
not by editing the upstream .dts (which OF_UPSTREAM ignores). A board-specific
-u-boot.dtsi shadows the generic sunxi-u-boot.dtsi, so include it explicitly to
keep the binman node (assembles u-boot-sunxi-with-spl.bin); then enable the USB
host controllers so OrangePi Zero can boot from USB.

--- /dev/null
+++ b/arch/arm/dts/sun8i-h2-plus-orangepi-zero-u-boot.dtsi
@@ -0,0 +1,12 @@
+// SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-2.0+
+// Armbian: enable USB host controllers in u-boot for USB boot on OrangePi Zero
+
+#include "sunxi-u-boot.dtsi"
+
+&ehci2 {
+	status = "okay";
+};
+
+&ohci2 {
+	status = "okay";
+};
